OL,3,CTributes to broadcasting legend Gerry
OL,4,CHarrison
OL,6,FTo a generation of football fans Gerry
OL,7,FHarrison, who has died at the age of
OL,8,F89, was one of the most recognisable
OL,9,Fvoices of the sport.
OL,11,FHarrison was a familiar face on TV
OL,12,Fscreens in the 1970s, 80s and 90s,
OL,13,Ffronting coverage not only for Anglia
OL,14,FTV's Match of the Week but also ITV
OL,15,FSport.
OL,17,FTributes have been pouring in for the
OL,18,Fman described as a "commentary great"
OL,19,Fand someone who helped change the way
OL,20,Ffootball was televised in Britain.
