OL,3,CTributes to broadcasting legend Gerry
OL,4,CHarrison
OL,6,FThe club's pen pictures from the
OL,7,Fprogramme in his debut season of 1962-
OL,8,F63 described him as: "New to Cheshire
OL,9,Fleague football this season. At
OL,10,Fpresent on the staff of the Daily
OL,11,FExpress but finding time to be one of
OL,12,Fthe fittest members of the team.
OL,13,FGaining experience with every game. A
OL,14,Fformer officer, having served in the
OL,15,Farmy."
OL,17,FHarrison entered the world of
OL,18,Fbroadcasting when he joined BBC Radio
OL,19,FMerseyside, but opportunity knocked in
OL,20,F1969 when he entered the football
OL,21,Fequivalent of Britain's Got Talent.
