OL,3,CTributes to broadcasting legend Gerry
OL,4,CHarrison
OL,6,F"People will remember him in the
OL,7,FAnglia region as a commentator and the
OL,8,Fpresenter of About Anglia, as it was
OL,9,Fin those days, as a sports presenter -
OL,10,Fbut beyond that he had a great ability
OL,11,Fto write so well for TV.
OL,13,F"If you ever sat down and saw one of
OL,14,Fhis scripts you would think 'Who on
OL,15,Fearth is going to make sense of that?'
OL,16,Fbut the way in which he wrote to
OL,17,Fpictures and the way which he could
OL,18,Fdeliver those scripts put him on a
OL,19,Fdifferent level.
